group.name: C=O
group.description: Parameters not final. Note these parameters are found to only accurately model 2-ketones

group.name: cN
group.description: The Joback ideal gas heat parameters, enthalpy of formation and entropy of formation for this group were not found.For the ideal gas heat capacity the same values as for cNH are used. For the enthalpy and entropy of formation the values have been set to 0.

group.name: COO-
group.description: The ideal gas heat capacity coefficients for ions are not available and have therefore been set to those of COOH. The enthalpy and entropy of formation are also not available and have been set 0.

group.name: H3O+

group.name: Na+
group.description: The ideal gas heat capacity coefficients for ions are not available and the correlation constant are thus set to produce a constant pressure ideal gas heat capacity of 5/2*R. The enthalpy and entropy of formation are also not available and have been set to 0.

group.name: CH3_adj
group.description: CH3_adj and CH2_adj are developed to accurately model acetates and propanoates. The CH3_adj and CH2_adj groups have different interactions with COO-, but all other unlike interactions are taken to be the same as CH2 and CH3. Note that in the databank only the interactions used in the reference are provided.

group.name: CH2OH_Short
group.description: CH2OH_Short introduced to accurate model the interaction of short-chain alcohols (ethanol and 1-propanol, n less than or equal to 3) or alkanolamines and water.

group.name: eO_Burger
group.description: eO_Burger is the end/terminal ether oxygen one CH3 group removed from the end of a molecule

group.name: mO_Burger
group.description: mO_Burger is the middle/centre ether oxygen between two CH2 groups

group.name: eO_Thiemann
group.description: Parameters not final. eO_Thiemann respresents the end/terminal ether oxygen one CH3 group removed from the end of a molecule. Note eO_Thiemann has the same like interactions as mO_Thiemann, but different unlike interactions. For polyethers this group is used in conjunction with CH2_OE when ether oxygens are seperated by 2 carbon atoms and CH2_OM when ether oxygens are separated by one carbon atom. In polyethers with ether oxygen separated by 3 or more carbons the normal CH2 group is used.

group.name: mO_Thiemann
group.description: Parameters not final. mO_Thiemann is the middle/centre ether oxygen in between two CH2 groups. Note mO_Thiemann has the same like interactions as eO_Thiemann, but different unlike interactions. For polyethers this group is used in conjunction with CH2_OE when ether oxygens are seperated by 2 carbon atoms and CH2_OM when ether oxygens are separated by one carbon atom. In polyethers with ether oxygen separated by 3 or more carbons the normal CH2 group is used.

group.name: CH2_OE
group.description: Parameters not final. CH2_OE is the oxyethylen group used in polyethers when there are exactly two carbon atoms between the ether oxygens. Note CH2_OE has the same like interactions as CH2, but different unlike interactions.

group.name: CH2_OM
group.description: Parameters not final. CH2_OM is the oxymethylen group used in polyethers when there is one carbon atom between the ether oxygens. Note CH2_OM has the same like interactions as CH2, but different unlike interactions.
